title: Incremental compilation ICE: Illegal read of 61996 in query system `dep_graph/graph.rs:430:25`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
This is an incremental compilation ICE, I found it when running `cargo test` on the Rocket repo (https://github.com/SergioBenitez/Rocket/commit/8cae077ba1d54b92cdef3e171a730b819d5eeb8e), though I've seen it happen on other repos, so I don't think it's anything specific to rocket. It goes away when I `cargo clean`. ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.60.0-nightly (a7e2e3396 2022-01-08) binary: rustc commit-hash: a7e2e33960e95d2eb1a2a2aeec169dba5f73de05 commit-date: 2022-01-08 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.60.0-nightly LLVM version: 13.0.0 ``` ### The output stack trace is *long*, I just included it in the backtrace below.
